We can leave people
and processes

00:22:01.630 --> 00:22:03.617
in better shape than
when we arrived there.

00:22:03.617 --> 00:22:05.200
It took me a long
time to learn that--

00:22:05.200 --> 00:22:07.600
I mean, I definitely had
some jobs where I'm like,

00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:11.090
you refill your own paper.

00:22:11.090 --> 00:22:13.720
I was out.

00:22:13.720 --> 00:22:17.860
Ink cartridge-- my
pie hole, you know?

00:22:17.860 --> 00:22:19.230
And then I left.

00:22:19.230 --> 00:22:23.430
And so, I'm really proud
of myself that I left.

00:22:23.430 --> 00:22:25.810
And I think that that's
really important,

00:22:25.810 --> 00:22:29.770
because as we sort
of conflate or we

00:22:29.770 --> 00:22:32.350
remove the space
between work and life,

00:22:32.350 --> 00:22:35.800
between fun and work,
that we actually

00:22:35.800 --> 00:22:39.400
have all of these
opportunities to create.

00:22:39.400 --> 00:22:42.400
So, I would like to do
something right now.

00:22:42.400 --> 00:22:46.930
I feel like we started at
